			<div class="description"><p>How do Zinn and Schweikart/Allen differ with regard to their discussion of Columbus? Is either interpretation different from the class lecture? You may want to consider these questions: Does either historian use the phrase "Old Worlds"? What kinds of language do the respective authors use? How do they characterize Columbus's arrival? Is it celebratory, or critical? How do  account for the differences?</p></div>
