				<!-- "description" class used for vCal microformat. -->
				<div class="description"> 
				<div class="writing"><h4>Writing</h4>			<div class="assignment-title">Blog Post #4: Representing the Civil War (Due October 19)</div>
			<div class="description"><p>For this assignment, find a movie on the American Civil War and/or its aftermath, and critique one aspect of the film. How do they represent the Civil War? What is the movie&#8217;s message and/or motivation? How does it <em>use</em> history to tell a story or to entertain? Finally, discuss how the movie and your critique of it compares with either Zinn or Schweikart/Allen. In what ways is the movie similar or different to how either book addresses the Civil War? Which is more persuasive? Why?</p>
<p>A few movies you might consider:</p>
<ul>
<li>Glory</li>
<li>CSA: The Confederate States of America</li>
<li>Gods and Generals</li>
<li>The Civil War: A Film by Ken Burns (<strong>Long</strong> documentary, so pick one section or chapter)</li>
<li>Gone with the Wind</li>
<li>Gettysburg</li>
<li>Cold Mountain</li>
</ul></div>
