				<div class="writing"><h4>Writing</h4>			<div class="assignment-title">Blog Post #5: Virginia Segregation Acts (Due October 26)</div>
			<div class="description"><p>Visit the campus library and find an act passed by the Virginia General Assembly, collected in the <em>Acts of Assembly</em>, between 1870 and 1940 that negotiates the rules and contexts of segregation, and an act that modifies or circumscribes the previous act. Write a post explaining what the acts legislate for or against, and in what contexts might the law come into question. Secondly, discuss how the two acts differ&mdash;How does the second act change the first act? Why do you think the change was necessary? What social or cultural interactions would the change in the law affect?</p></div>
