		<div class="summary">Evidence&mdash;Images</div>
				<!-- "description" class used for vCal microformat. -->
				<div class="description"> 
				<div class="writing"><h4>Writing</h4>			<div class="assignment-title">Blog Post #7: Imaging Consumerism (Due November 9)</div>
			<div class="description"><p>How do images in advertising reflect a particular theme at the turn of the century? What kinds of techniques, themes, and catchphrases did advertisers at the turn of the last century use to promote their products? In this assignment, you will create a photo album of 4-6 photos in your TypePad account, using images of ads from <a href="http://memory.loc.gov">American Memory</a>. This will be a â€œminiâ€ version of what you will create for your National Mall photo album. Think carefully about how you will order your photos, how you will transition your narrative from one photo to the next. When you finish you album, write a blog post that introduces your album and provides a link to it.</p></div>
		</div>					</div>
				</div>
