		<div class="summary">Collecting History</div>
				<!-- "description" class used for vCal microformat. -->
				<div class="description"> 
				<div class="writing"><h4>Writing</h4>			<div class="assignment-title">Blog Post #10: 9/11 Digital Archive (Due December 14)</div>
			<div class="description"><p>Visit the <a href="http://911.gmu.edu/">September 11 Digital Archive</a> and read a few of the entries to get a sense of how people remember events and their reactions. In your blog post, discuss a particular theme or issue that some entries have in common. A few questions to address: How do people remember September 11? What specific things do they remember? Finally, speculate on collecting memories in general, and how collecting memories of events such as September 11 can aid or hinder historians 30-50 years from now.</p></div>
		</div>					</div>
